name: Drew Lock
summary: The New York Giants will likely start Drew Lock at quarterback in Week 13 against the Dallas Cowboys, as Tommy DeVito is injured and unavailable. Lock's performance as a starter in 2024 has been criticized by NFL executives, who believe it lacks sense. Lock's contract incentives could be affected by DeVito's injury, potentially leading to a substantial payout. Despite his past struggles, Lock is expected to start on Thanksgiving against the Cowboys. He previously requested guidance from injured teammate Daniel Jones and has studied the opposing defense extensively. The Giants' decision to start Lock over DeVito has surprised many, and his performance will be closely scrutinized.

name: Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade
summary: The Macy's Thanksgiving Day Parade, an iconic annual tradition, will feature a star-studded lineup in 2024, including Jennifer Hudson and Cynthia Erivo. Live coverage will be available on NBC News, TODAY, and local news outlets, providing viewers with all the latest news, performances, and updates on the parade's progress. This year's parade will showcase an array of floats, performances, and special guests, with millions of spectators expected to line the streets and tune in for the spectacle. NPR has provided an in-depth look at the logistics and preparation that goes into bringing the parade to life, while other sources have detailed the channel information and streaming options for those planning to watch from home. Despite a forecast of cold and rainy weather, the parade is expected to proceed as planned, with participants and spectators alike determined to celebrate the 98th anniversary of this cherished event.

name: Is Walmart open on Thanksgiving
summary: Many major retailers including Walmart have adjusted their store hours for Thanksgiving in recent years due to employee feedback and customer preference for spending the holiday with family and friends. In 2024, Walmart will remain closed on Thanksgiving Day, November 28th, to allow employees to enjoy the holiday with their loved ones. However, the store will reopen with extended hours on Black Friday, November 29th. Other major retailers such as Target and Costco will also be closed on Thanksgiving Day, while some grocery stores, convenience stores, and restaurants may have modified hours. It's always a good idea to check with your local store or visit their website for specific holiday hours to confirm.
